description: A Quint made from Gemshorn pipes, of 10-2/3', 5-1/3', 2-2/3', or 1-1/3' pitch. Regnier gives the synonym Cylinder-Quinte, but probably incorrectly.
examplesDescription: Osiris contains seven examples of Gemshornquint[e], one at 10-2/3' pitch and the rest at 2-2/3', and a dozen examples of Gemsquinte, five at 2-2/3' pitch and seven at 1-1/3'. Nearly all date from the 20th century. No examples are known of Quintgemshorn (mentioned only by Adlung).
